
PHASE 1 — Git & GitHub Basics (1–2 weeks)
-------------------------------------------
Course 1 : Google Git & GitHub Course : https://www.skills.google/paths/2472/course_templates/1343?utm_source=chatgpt.com

          ONLY learn:
          
          what is git
          repository
          clone
          commit
          push
          pull
          branch
          merge
          pull request

Course 2 : GitHub Skills - Introduction to GitHub : https://github.com/skills/introduction-to-github?utm_source=chatgpt.com
This is hands-on.

        You’ll practice:
        
        repos
        issues
        branches
        commits
        PRs

Course 3 : Review Pull Requests : https://github.com/skills/review-pull-requests?utm_source=chatgpt.com

        Learn:
        
        PR review process
        approvals
        comments
        merges
        
        VERY important for engineering workflow.

Course 4 : Reolve Merge Conflicts : https://github.com/skills/resolve-merge-conflicts?utm_source=chatgpt.com

        Learn:
        
        merge conflicts
        conflict resolution
        branch syncing
        
        That’s enough Git/GitHub basics.

PHASE 2 — GitHub Actions + CI/CD (2 weeks)
-------------------------------------------

NOW move into engineering workflows.

Course 5 : Hello GitHub Actions: https://github.com/skills/hello-github-actions?utm_source=chatgpt.com

          Learn:
          
          workflow YAML
          triggers
          jobs
          steps
          automation
          
          THIS is your introduction to CI/CD.

Course 6 : Test with GitHub Actions : https://github.com/skills/test-with-actions?utm_source=chatgpt.com

          Learn:
          
          automated testing
          CI pipelines
          running workflows automatically
          
          This is what interviewers mean by:
          
          “Do you know CI/CD?”


Course 7 : GitHub Secrets Exercise : https://github.com/githubtraining/exercise-use-secrets?utm_source=chatgpt.com

          Learn:
          
          GitHub Secrets
          encrypted credentials
          environment variables
          secure pipelines
          
          VERY useful for cloud/data jobs.

PHASE 3 — Build Something Tiny (MOST IMPORTANT)
          
          After those courses:
          
          Create your own GitHub repo.
          
          Example:
          
          sql-learning-project
          
          Add:
          
          SQL scripts
          README
          simple Python file later
          
          Then:
          
          create branch
          commit changes
          open PR
          merge PR
          add GitHub Action
          add secret
          
          THIS is where confidence comes from.
